diversity works at stanford university message from the president student affairs diversity works at stanford students faculty and staff alumni service programs additional resources stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit message from the president message from the president tuesday november 23 2010 from its earliest days stanford university has been committed to founder jane stanford's promise to resist the tendency of stratification of society by keeping open an avenue whereby the deserving and the exceptional may rise through their own efforts we believe that the richness of our backgrounds cultures talents and interests has made stanford university one of the world's leading research and teaching institutions today our commitment to diversity is stronger than ever before that commitment is reflected in the wide range of offices services policies and programs that help us attract and retain faculty students and staff who bring a multiplicity of experiences perspectives and interests we realize that a variety of approaches are necessary to foster diversity throughout the university and we will continue to give careful attention to these important efforts in doing so stanford will remain on the cutting edge in the search for new knowledge and in creating leaders for the next century john hennessy acts of intolerance protocol to report an incident please use our online form student affairs the student affairs division is responsible for programs and services that focus on students and their stanford experience while also engaging with faculty staff parents alumni and the community at large copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
